description:
For sale: $295,000. Home was essentially all new when bought in '16 and only improved since with updated baths, fresh paint & new roof & water softener.  Rest of mechanicals are all updated as are windows and appliances.  All this on a large corner lot that is wonderfully treed, flat, and recently irrigated.

Spacious main floor boasts functional kitchen with solid surface counters, newer stainless steel appliances and loads of storage including pantry; dining space with easy access to huge backyard; sun filled living room, 2 bedrooms, and completely updated bath round out this level...

Park with trails and woods is only a half block away and Rice Lake Reserve is with-in biking distance boasting miles of trails, access to lakes & nature center/camping options.  Everything else close too with Target, Kohls, and Wal-Mart all about a mile away along with numerous other shops, restaurants and gym/fitness options.

One of the biggest lots in the neighborhood and huge park with trails only a block away is where this wonderful split sits. Don't let foundation size fool you because it feels big with over-sized foyer boasting coat closet and some room to use it, large gathering spaces, and good sized bedrooms and baths. Feel free to contact Agent with any questions...

Tons of bike/walk trails to library, shops, rest & more. 3 car heated and insulated garage, large deck overlooking private, treed lot, raised panel oak cabinets, some stainless steel appliances, 3 bedrooms on one level, updated mechanicals, newer energy efficient furnace, water heater, A/C, new garage doors & openers, walk-in closets & tons or storage throughout. Home has so much potential and is located on a gorgeous private lot w/lake views on a quiet cul-de-sac. This is a neighborhood everyone is waiting to get into! Enjoy lake life close to the cities!
Recently sold: $182,500.

You're not just getting a home, you are getting the best community.
